-----Original Appointment-----
From: Camille O'Jeer
Sent: 11 October 2013 10:58
To: Camille O'Jeer; Jo Tomlinson; Williams, Nicola; Wilson, Darrell; Taslim Nasser; Faythe King; Angela Rivett; Dawn Slater; Eoin Kearney; Sue Farmer; Tait, Andrew; Manpreet Laanda; Ryan Bloom; Georgina Karnessi; Terry, Jessica; Raymond, Chloe; Emily Delehanty; Gabriella Clark; Xhanan Goleshi; Katie Ellwood-Smith; D'Herlincourt, Sixtine; Hayette Oudia; Neal Patel; Victoria Smith; Roier, Christian; Bhinder, Simran; Natasha Steenkamp; Rebecca Jasper; Herbst, Leslie; Mark Edwards; Amanda Macbeth; Louise Lee; Reed, Jonathan; Leanne Sweeney; Skirmante Millington; Viveka Thakker; Shaun Kelly; Jim Higginson; Duncan Turner; georgekwalker@hotmail.co.uk<mailto:georgekwalker@hotmail.co.uk>; canarywharf.sas; bluewater.sas; Podan, Sophie; Cecilia Kwofie; regentstreet.sas; brentcross.sas; Katherine Lowry
Subject: Jo and Abike's Leaving Party
When: 01 November 2013 17:30-21:00 (UTC) Dublin, Edinburgh, Lisbon, London.
Where: Freedom Bar, 66 Wardour Street, Soho, London, W1F 0TA


Morning All! ☺

As I am sure you all know by now, Jo is breaking up the best UK marketing team that ever existed, also known as the dynamic duo ‘Camillio and Josephine’ on Thursday 31st October. And, Abike also takes her fabulousness away from us on Friday 1st November to start her new adventure in welcoming her totes amaze little man into the world.

To say good luck, good bye, farewell and all that good stuff to them both, I invite you all to ‘Freedom’ to raise our glasses!

I am sure I have forgotten some people, so please feel free to pass the invite on!
See you all there! ☺

In this session, we will present an assortment of tips and tricks to use while working with Unity. These tips and tricks could make our experience in Unity better, faster, stronger or they could just keep us amused. We could simply be reminded of the obvious or we could be presented with something we've never heard of, thought of or imagined. Like entering a flea market or wild bazaar, we will hunt around and try to find something for everyone, even if everything we present isn't useful to all. Tutor: Adam Buckner

National Speed Awareness – Confirmation and receipt
We are pleased to confirm that a place has been reserved for you on the National Speed Awareness course as follows:
Venue: Mercure London Watford Hotel A41 Watford Bypass Watford Hertfordshire, WD25 8JH
Date: Friday 9th October 2015
Time: Starting at 1.30pm, finishing at 5.30pm
Please arrive at least 15 minutes before the start to allow time for parking and registration. Note that late arrivals cannot be admitted. You must bring your driving licence and photo-ID with you.
Your payment of £85.00 is acknowledged. The course fee includes tea/coffee on arrival and about halfway through the session.
You should use your best endeavours to attend on time without putting yourself or others at risk. Allow plenty of time for the journey. If the weather conditions are severe, please check that the course is going ahead by calling the reception number of the venue where your course is being held (shown on the map of the venue). If your course is cancelled, we will contact you afterwards to arrange a new date for the course.
Parking is free of charge at the venue – upon arrival you must report to Reception and provide your vehicle registration number to avoid charges.
We would remind you that full attendance and active participation are required. Please read through the course checklist attached to this email prior to attending. Mobile phones and other electronic devices must be switched off during the course sessions.
If you need to change the course you are booked on, you may be able to do so online through the following link: www.hertsdirect.org/drive but this will depend on a place being available on another course within the time limit set by the Police and there will be a charge as follows:
- £25 if the change is made 7 days or less, but more than 1 working day before the course date
- £45 if the change is made one working day before the course date or on the day of the course

Benihana restaurant in London’s Piccadilly offers a truly unique dining experience. The show-stopping chefs with their dancing knives and witty banter originated in New York in the 60’s and Behihana’s culinary experience has been enjoyed by more than 100 million diners worldwide. Each of Behinana’s large shared table enjoys its own dedicated chef who prepares a light, delicious, many-coursed Japanese meal teppan-yaki style before your eyes while entertaining you with samurai knife skills and a stream of charming patter. You can choose from several kinds of steak, chicken, or seafood and let the chef take care of the rest. Meals at Benihana are terrific fun for families, groups of friends and outings for work teams as well as easy first-date venues. The décor is modern Japanese, smart and minimalist. Service is charming and, if sushi is always part of your Japanese meal, Benihana’s sushi is an excellent example of authentic Japanese cuisine.
